'''Tonging''' refers to the action of seizing, grabbing, holding, or manipulating a given object with [[tongs]]. "Tonging" is a form of the transitive [[verb]] "to tong." A tong is a [[doodad]] with two [[handles]] which enables a [[person]] to grab an [[object]] from a distance (usually around 10 inches) using the apparatus known as the "tong head," which is usually made of [[metal]] and attatches to the handles of the tong. Tongs also easily allow for the [[transportation]] of objects held between the parts of the tong head. They are often used for cooking purposes, particularly for moving [[food]] such as [[hamburger]] patties and [[hot dogs]] atop a [[grill]].
In the [[American]] [[sub-culture]] of the tag world, "tonging" describes the action of seizing an object with tongs for the purpose of pictorially documenting the [[event]]. Some people use the pictures from this "tonging" and keep them in a [[book]] for the pupose of recording [[vacations]], specific [[time periods]], or important [[dates]]. Espeically in the [[South]], tonging occurs amongst [[high school]] seniors to document amusing or sentimental moments in certain [[groups]] of students' last year of [[secondary schooling]].